{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2012}} '''Anthony Carr''' (born 6 December 1943) is a Canadian [[psychic]]. He was once referred to by [[Jacqueline Stallone]] as the "World's Most Documented Psychic".<ref name="TheSpectrum2017">{{cite web | title=Anthony Carr: Psychic to the stars | website=The Spectrum & Daily News | date=2017-09-05 | url=https://www.thespectrum.com/story/entertainment/2017/09/05/anthony-carr-psychic-stars/633942001/ | access-date=2018-08-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/19159197.html?dids=19159197:19159197&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Dec+28%2C+1996&author=&pub=Toronto+Star&desc=Psychic+looks+to+the+future+Anthony+Carr+predicts+Madonna+Oscar%2C+uprising+of+Ontario%27s+poor&pqatl=google|title=Psychic looks to the future Anthony Carr predicts Madonna Oscar, uprising of Ontario's poor|accessdate=1 November 2009 | date=28 December 1996 |newspaper= [[Toronto Star]] |page= H3 |edition= Final |subscription=yes |via= [[ProQuest]]}}</ref>
== About ==
He became most notable for allegedly predicting the [[September 11 attacks]] when, in December 2000, he said that he foresees a "cataclysmic cosmic event" the following year and to "Watch for a sign in the heavens. It will shock the whole world," and will "put the fear of God in us."<ref>{{cite news |url= https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/427260361.html?dids=427260361:427260361&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Dec+31%2C+2000&author=Carola+Vyhnak&pub=Toronto+Star&desc=2001+%27will+put+fear+of+God+in+us%2C%27+psychic+says+%3B+Anthony+Carr+foresees+%27cataclysmic+cosmic+event%27+shocking+world&pqatl=google|title=2001 'will put fear of God in us,' psychic says ; Anthony Carr foresees 'cataclysmic cosmic event' shocking world|newspaper= [[Toronto Star]] |edition= Ontario |page= 1 |accessdate=1 November 2009 | first= Carola | last= Vyhnak |date= 31 December 2000 |subscription= yes |via= [[ProQuest]]}}</ref> He has been claimed to have predicted several other events. However, he has received criticism for many of his predictions not coming true.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.csicop.org/specialarticles/show/failed_psychic_predictions_1999/ |title= Failed psychic predictions 1999 |last= Emery |first= Gene |date= 31 December 1999 |magazine= [[Skeptical Inquirer]] |accessdate= 18 March 2014 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20091111112102/http://www.csicop.org/specialarticles/show/failed_psychic_predictions_1999/| archivedate= 11 November 2009 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url= http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=NewsLibrary&p_multi=DSNB&d_place=DSNB&p_theme=newslibrary2&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0F360580FB5916D1&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM |title= Psychic missed targets in 1991, so writer takes a shot at 1992 |newspaper= [[Deseret News]] |accessdate= 1 November 2009 | date= 1 January 1992 |via= [[NewsLibrary]] |subscription= yes}}</ref>
