{{distinguish|Dama language (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox language |name=Dama |nativename= |states=[[Sierra Leone]] |extinct=1930s |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam1=[[Niger–Congo languages|Niger–Congo]] |fam2=[[Mande languages|Mande]] ? |fam3=... |fam4=Vai–Kono ? |iso3=none |glotto=dama1262 |glottorefname=Dama }}
'''Dama''' is an extinct language of [[Sierra Leone]]. It was replaced by [[Mende language|Mende]]. Based on a few remembered words and toponyms, Dalby (1963) believed it to be a Northern [[Mande language]], similar to Kono and Vai, but ''Glottolog'' leaves it unclassified.
