{{Infobox language |name=Faita |altname=Kulsab |states=[[Papua New Guinea]] |region= [[Madang Province]] |speakers=50 |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=[[Trans–New Guinea]] |fam2=[[Madang languages|Madang]] |fam3=[[Southern Adelbert Range languages|Southern Adelbert]] |fam4=Sogeram |fam5=East |iso3=faj |glotto=fait1240 |glottorefname=Faita }}
'''Faita''', or '''Kulsab''', is a divergent and nearly extinct [[Madang languages|Madang language]] of the [[Adelbert Range]] of [[Papua New Guinea]]. It was once placed in the now-defunct [[Brahman languages|Brahman]] branch of Madang.
