'''Komi Lje''' (Ԉ&nbsp;ԉ; italics: <span style="font-family: times, Times New Roman, serif; font-size: larger">''Ԉ&nbsp;ԉ''</span>) is a letter of the [[Molodtsov alphabet]], a variant of [[Cyrillic script|Cyrillic]]. It was used only in the writing of the [[Komi language]]. It is equivalent to the [[Lje|Cyrillic letter Lje]] (Љ&nbsp;љ).{{citation needed | date=May 2011 | reason=Љ or ЛЬ? }} Some of its forms are similar to the [[Radical 16]] (几).

