{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] --> | name = Prabhas Kumar Choudhary [[File:PKChaudhary.jpg|thumb|Prabhas Kumar Choudhary]] | birth_date = {{birth date|1941|1|2|df=y}} | birth_place = Pindaruch | death_date = {{death date and age|1998|2|22|1941|1|2|df=y}} | death_place = [[Kolkata]], [[West Bengal]] | occupation = Writer, Editor and Publisher | nationality = Indian | period = 20th century }}
'''Prabhas Kumar Choudhary'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mithilatimes.com/maithili-literature/|title=Maithili Literature|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=KnPoYxrRfc0C&pg=PA4053&lpg=PA4053&dq=prabhas+kumar+chaudhary&source=bl&ots=Y7MzB8jGAW&sig=7GCicuFq04iNLu_p6L_b2uM4dhY&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj6ipefgeHMAhWFnZQKHUQvDL4Q6AEIVDAP#v=onepage&q=prabhas%20kumar%20chaudhary&f=false|title=Encyclopaedia of Indian Literature|publisher=}}</ref> (प्रभास कुमार चौधरी, 2 January 1941 – 22 February 1998) was an Indian author, editor and publisher known for his novels and short stories, written in Maithili and Hindi languages. He had a short but remarkable life as he received the '''[[Sahitya Akademi Award]] for [[Maithili language]] in 1990 for Prabhasak Katha''', a collection of short stories and authored other books. He also won the '''Vaidehi Puraskar''' in 1982 for his book Raja Pokhair Me Katek Machri.
==Life== Born, in '''Pindaruch''', to '''Shri Surendra Choudhary''' and '''Smt. Kali Choudhary''' in a zamindar family, he was the eldest of his nine siblings. People used to affectionately call him Hadbad Babu. He came from a modest background. He did his matriculation from '''M L Academy, [[Darbhanga]]''' and did a double M.A. in Political Science and History from '''[[Patna University]]'''.
He was married to '''Smt. Jyotsna Choudhary''' (1947-1995) and is survived by his six children, two brothers and four sisters. He died of a heart attack at the age of fifty-seven in Kolkata, West Bengal.
==Career== He joined '''[[Life Insurance Corporation of India]]''' in 1966 as Assistant Administrative Officer and had risen to the rank of Regional Manager - Marketing (Eastern Zone) at the time of his death.
==Major Works== * Bahar Ijot Bhitar Dhuan, Mithila Mihir (Magazine), 1961. Maithili. * '''Nav Ghar Uthay: Purn Ghar Khasay'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=C0f898HDLAYC&pg=PA185&lpg=PA185&dq=prabhas+kumar+chaudhary&source=bl&ots=GAd4IjI-zr&sig=PewQ7H1nxS66EZWQgoMxFSkRlsc&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj6ipefgeHMAhWFnZQKHUQvDL4Q6AEIIzAC#v=onepage&q=prabhas%20kumar%20chaudhary&f=false|title=A Survey of Maithili Literature|publisher=}}</ref> (Short Stories), 1964. Maithili. * Abhishapt, Jyotsna Prakashan 1970. Maithili. * Yugpurush, Jyotsna Prakashan 1971. Maithili. * '''Humra Lag Rahab''',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=m1R2Pa3f7r0C&pg=PA228&lpg=PA228&dq=prabhas+kumar+chaudhary&source=bl&ots=uprb1-2zGJ&sig=nx-blx-tCNdDRRFfQDTRUzKpn_A&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj6ipefgeHMAhWFnZQKHUQvDL4Q6AEIGzAA#v=onepage&q=prabhas%20kumar%20chaudhary&f=false|title=Modern Indian Literature, an Anthology: Surveys and poems|publisher=}}</ref> Maithili Akademi 1977. Maithili. * Navarambh, 1979. Maithili. * '''Raja Pokhair Me Katek Machri''', Jyotsna Prakashan 1981. Maithili. (Translated in Hindi by Smt. Vibha Rani)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindibook.com/index.php?p=sr&Uc=HB-26663|title=hindibook.com: RAJA POKHARE MEIN KITANI MACHALIYAN PRABHAS KUMAR CHAUDHARY HB|publisher=}}</ref> (Won him the Vaidehi Puraskar, 1982) * '''Katha Prabhas''', Maithili Akademi 1988. Maithili. * '''Prabhasak Katha''', Jyotsna Prakashan 1989. Maithili. * Ashtavakrak Shesh Katha, 1997. Maithili. * '''Didbal''', 2004 (Post Humous) Jyotsna Prakashan. Maithili * And many other short stories in Hindi published in various magazines.
