There are at least four translations of the [[Tirukkural]] available in [[Russian language|Russian]].
==History== The joint effort of J. J. Glazov and A. Krishnamurthi resulted in the first Russian translation of the Kural text, published in 1963.<ref>{{cite book | last = Sanjeevi | first = N. | author-link = | title = ''Bibliography on Tirukkural''. ''In'' First All India Tirukkural Seminar Papers | publisher = University of Madras | series = | volume = | edition = | date = 1973 | location = Chennai | pages = 147–148 | language = | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref> The [[Tirukkural translations into English|English translation]] of select couplets by [[C. Rajagopalachari]] was translated into Russian by D. V. Burba. This contains translation of 555 couplets from the first two divisions (Virtue and Wealth). In 1990, another translation of the complete text was made by Vithali Furniki, a translator in the [[Centre of Indian Cultural Studies, Moscow|Centre of Indian Cultural Studies]], [[Moscow]].<ref name="Furniki_1990">{{cite web | url = http://www.tirukkural.narod.ru/ | title = Тируккурал | last = Furniki | first = Vithali | date = 1990 | website = | publisher = | access-date = 14 April 2017 | quote = }}</ref><ref name="GeoCities">{{cite web | url = http://www.geocities.ws/nvkashraf/kur-trans/Rus-Int.htm | title = Тируккурал: Святое Откровение Тамилов | last = Ashraf | first = N. V. K. | date = 1990 | website = GeoCities | publisher = | access-date = 14 April 2017 | quote = }}</ref>
==Translations== {| class="wikitable" |- !style="text-align:center; width:25%;" rowspan="2"|Translation !colspan="2"|Chapter 26, Избегать вкушения мяса |- !''Kural'' 254 (Couplet 26:4) !''Kural'' 258 (Couplet 26:8) |- | style="text-align:center;"|''Vithali Furniki, 1990''||Если вы спросите себя, что такое добродетель и сострадание, то знайте — это неубиение. Убийство же есть отсутствие сострадания, а грех — вкушение мяса. ||У кого ясный взор и отсутствуют пороки, тот не станет поедать плоть другого существа, лишенного жизни ради того, чтобы быть съеденным |}
